All builds and tests pass. Here's a summary of what was implemented:

**`internal/repository/config.go`** — Added `DbCacheSizeMB` (default 2048MB) and `DbSoftHeapLimitMB` (default 16384MB) fields to `RepositoryConfig`.

**`internal/repository/dbConnection.go`** — Replaced hardcoded `_cache_size=-200000` with config-driven value; changed `setupSqlite()` to accept config and use `DbSoftHeapLimitMB` for the soft heap limit; added startup log line showing effective SQLite settings.

**`internal/config/config.go`** — Added `DbConfig` struct with JSON-tagged fields and a `DbConfig` pointer field on `ProgramConfig`.

**`internal/config/schema.go`** — Added `"db-config"` JSON schema section for validation.

**`cmd/cc-backend/main.go`** — Wired `repository.SetConfig()` in `initDatabase()`, applying any `db-config` overrides from config.json before connecting.

Without `db-config` in config.json, the new defaults (2GB cache/conn, 16GB soft heap) apply. With it, operators can tune all values:

```json
{
  "main": {
    "db-config": {
      "cache-size-mb": 16384,
      "soft-heap-limit-mb": 131072,
      "max-open-connections": 8,
      "max-idle-time-minutes": 30
    }
  }
}
```
